1015560	43	0	17	108	CONF	-187	211	74	43	63	26	0	0	0	0	0	0	0	0	-8762	0	true	34	0	0	0	0	103	5	20	103	54	0	168	100	22	95	0	Unrealized Gains / Losses on Derivatives	Net Service Fee from Affiliates	Loan Servicing Fees	OCC Assessment Fee	Insurance	Foreclosure Expenses						Push down accounting adjustment		The Industrial and Commercial Bank of China acquired control of the Bank on July 6, 2012 in a transaction in which it acquired 80% of the voting shares of the Bank and the selling shareholder, The Bank of East Asia, Limited, retained 20%. In connection with this transaction, the Bank implemented push down accounting, which applies to the books of the Bank the purchase accounting adjustments that the controlling shareholder makes to include the Bank in its consolidated financial statements. These adjustments involve recording the identified tangible and intangible assets and liabilities of the Bank at their fair value as of the transaction date and recognizing goodwill as the amount by which the consideration paid to acquire the shares transferred exceeds the proportionate share of the net fair value of the Bank's identified tangible and intangible assets and liabilities. Accordingly, the Report of Income includes the operations of the Bank only from the transaction date to the reporting date.

Since these financial institutions were both wholly-owned subsidiaries of a common parent corporation, this call report reflects the Encore and Cadence Banks' combined statement of condition and results of operations as of and for the period ended September 30, 2012.
